list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: (of an object, especially a ball) move quickly up, back, or away from a surface after hitting it; rebound (once or repeatedly).
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: the ball bounced away and he chased it
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Bóng bị trả lại và anh ta đuổi theo nó

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: (of a person) jump repeatedly up and down, typically on something springy.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: bouncing up and down on the mattress

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: (of a check) be returned by a bank when there are insufficient funds to meet it.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: tiền thuê của tôi séc bị trả lại

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: eject (a troublemaker) forcibly from a nightclub or similar establishment.
a rebound of a ball or other object.
an act of jumping or an instance of being moved up and down.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: every bounce of the truck brought them into fresh contact
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: mỗi chiếc xe tải mang chúng vào tiếp xúc tươi sống
